GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
SESSION 2025
S 3
SENATE BILL 229
Judiciary Committee Substitute Adopted 4/30/25
House Committee Substitute Favorable 5/6/26
Short Title: College Sports Updates. (Public)
Sponsors:
Referred to:
March 5, 2025
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO EXEMPT RECORDS CONTAINING REVENUE SHARING INFORMATION
3 FROM PUBLIC RECORDS REQUIREMENTS; TO ALLOW CONSTITUENT
4 INSTITUTIONS TO CLASSIFY ALL GRADUATE STUDENT-ATHLETES RECEIVING
5 FULL SCHOLARSHIPS AS NORTH CAROLINA RESIDENTS FOR TUITION
6 PURPOSES; TO EXPAND PERMITTED SALE OF ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES IN
7 CONNECTION WITH UNIVERSITY SPONSORED SPORTS EVENTS; AND TO
8 REMOVE CERTAIN LIMITATIONS ON RAFFLES CONDUCTED BY CONSTITUENT
9 INSTITUTIONS AND ASSOCIATED NONPROFIT ORGANIZATIONS.
10 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
11
12 PART I. EXEMPT RECORDS CONTAINING REVENUE SHARING INFORMATION
13 FROM PUBLIC RECORDS REQUIREMENTS
14 SECTION 1. G.S. 132-1.2 reads as rewritten:
15 "§ 132-1.2. Confidential information.
16 Nothing in this Chapter shall be construed to require or authorize a public agency or its
17 subdivision to disclose any information that:
18 …
19 (12) Reveals records held by a constituent institution of The University of North
20 Carolina containing information pertaining to the constituent institution's (i)
21 overall revenue sharing budget, (ii) allocations of its revenue sharing budget
22 by team or program, or (iii) allocations of its revenue sharing budget to
23 individual student-athletes. For the purposes of this subdivision, "revenue
24 sharing budget" means the revenue that a constituent institution has authorized
25 to be paid to student-athletes."
26
27 PART II. CLASSIFY GRADUATE STUDENT-ATHLETES RECEIVING FULL
28 SCHOLARSHIPS AS NORTH CAROLINA RESIDENTS
29 SECTION 2. G.S. 116-143.6 reads as rewritten:
30 "§ 116-143.6. Full scholarship students attending constituent institutions.
31 (a) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, if the Board of Trustees of a constituent
32 institution of The University of North Carolina elects to do so, it may by resolution adopted
33 consider as residents of North Carolina all persons who receive full scholarships to the institution
34 from entities recognized by the institution and attend the institution as undergraduate or graduate
*S229-v-3*

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 students. The aforesaid persons shall be considered residents of North Carolina for all purposes
2 by The University of North Carolina.
3 …."
4
5 PART III. EXPAND PERMITTED SALE OF ALCOHOLIC BEVERAGES IN
6 CONNECTION WITH COLLEGE SPORTS EVENTS
7 SECTION 3. G.S. 18B-1006(a) reads as rewritten:
8 "§ 18B-1006. Miscellaneous provisions on permits.
9 (a) School and College Campuses. – No permit for the sale of alcoholic beverages shall
10 be issued to a business on the campus or property of a public school, college, or university. This
11 subsection shall not apply to the following:
12 …
13 (10) A stadium, athletic facility, or arena on the campus or property of a public
14 college or university, if the Board of Trustees of the public college or
15 university has voted to allow the issuance of permits for use at that stadium,
16 athletic facility, or arena. If a Board of Trustees votes to allow the issuance of
17 permits in accordance with this subdivision, the Board of Trustees shall
18 provide written notice to the Commission that it has voted to allow the
19 issuance of permits. Any permit described in G.S. 18B-1001, 18B-1002(a)(2),
20 or 18B-1002(a)(5) may be issued pursuant to this subdivision to applicants
21 meeting the requirements for the requested permit. Notwithstanding the
22 issuance of a mixed beverages permit pursuant to G.S. 18B-1001(10), this
23 subdivision does not authorize the sale of mixed beverages when the stadium,
24 athletic facility, or arena is being used for a sports event sponsored by the
25 public college or university. This subdivision does not apply to any sales
26 authorized under subdivisions (1) through (8) of this subsection. For purposes
27 of this subdivision, the premises of a stadium, athletic facility, or arena shall
28 include any area that meets all of the following requirements:
29 a. Is either of the following:
30 1. Is within 500 feet of the furthest exterior building wall,
31 perimeter fence, or permanent fixed perimeter.perimeter of the
32 stadium, athletic facility, or arena.
33 2. Is within a designated satellite area on the campus or property
34 of the public college or university during the period of time
35 beginning six hours before a sports event sponsored by the
36 public college or university in the stadium, athletic facility, or
37 arena and ending three hours after the conclusion of the sports
38 event.
39 b. Is designated by the stadium, athletic facility, or arena in a map or
40 written description that clearly defines the boundary of the area, and
41 that map or written description is included in the permit application.
42 c. Can be designated in a manner that enables the stadium, athletic
43 facility, or arena to ensure compliance with the provisions of this
44 Chapter.
45 …."
46
47 PART IV. REMOVE LIMITATIONS ON CERTAIN RAFFLES
48 SECTION 4. G.S. 14-309.15 reads as rewritten:
49 "§ 14-309.15. Raffles.
50 …
Page 2 Senate Bill 229-Third Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (i) The restrictions in subsections (c) through (g) of this section do not apply to raffles
2 conducted by constituent institutions of The University of North Carolina or nonprofit
3 organizations affiliated with a constituent institution of The University of North Carolina."
4
5 PART V. EFFECTIVE DATE
6 SECTION 5. This act is effective when it becomes law and applies beginning with
7 the 2026-2027 academic year.
